				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Weapons with Instrument augments<a name="12246"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 17 03 10:01 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Troubadors mace is Brass not percussion, so no, it won't be faster than your walrus drum.
<br />

<br />
Most weapons with instrument mods the mods are not even as good as a plain instrument, the benifit of having the weapon tho is that you can sing songs that normally &quot;require&quot; an instrument without having to put your weapons away.  They also enhance songs as well.
<br />

<br />
I use my troubadors mace with McVaxius Berserker Crescendo, so that I get some additional stats when sung.
<br />

<br />
I also have a Gem Inlaid Longsword, which does have the percussion skill on it, but it's not much faster than singing without a drum.....  I had read that it was faster than Walrun Skin, so saved up the money to buy it only to be disappointed.  Tho I will admit, the sword is an awesome sword, so not real disappointed.  I do get a few extra points dmg from DoT's when I have it equipped.
<br />

<br />

<br />
As far as I know, no weapon's instrument mod is even close to the best of the instruments.  Tho with LDoN augments, who knows, maybe it's possible down the road.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Aanuvenea lvl 49 bard of Cazic Thule
<br />
Woohoo, 2.5 min selos rocks!!!!
<br />
</span></td>
