				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Weapons with Instrument augments<a name="12247"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Nov 17 03 10:04 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok, first off, Troub mace is brass, not percussion, but essentially you are fight. It has the same instrument base (modification) as a storebought horn, so you do not need to equip a horn to get the horn benefits (unless you want a higher modification than 1.8).  Lastly you do have to have it equiped to make use of it, so you can use it meleeing.
<br />

<br />
I still use my Troub mace both to melee and when chant kiting to get the stats and brass mod ( until I get my epic that is ).
<br />

<br />
GL to you!
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian
<br />
</span></td>
