				<td colspan="2"><span>I've seen the Gem Inlaid Longsword 10k for sale at a higher rate than the Battle Drummer's Main-Gauche 7k in the Bazaar. I lucked out and got both Battle-Drummers Main Gauche and Thunderous Drums of Karana for 3,500 each. Seeing as I'm a member of a casual guild and am a casual player, not too shabby. I do not understand why anyone would want to purchase the sword. 
<br />

<br />
Battle Drummer Main-Gauche = 11dmg / 17dly dmg bonus 12, DEX +5, STA +5, CHA +5, Mana +40, Sv Magic +8 ADDS 100% to Percussion Songs (2.0 on Reed's)
<br />

<br />
Gem Inlaid Longsword = 11dmg / 19dly dmg bonus 13, DEX +4, CHA +5, INT +4, Sv Disease +8, HP +20, Mana +15 ADDS 40% to Percussion Songs (1.4 on Reed's)
<br />

<br />
I usually dual wield with Legendary Dagger of Might and can do some pretty decent damage while still providing some nice percussion tunes to my group. 
<br />

<br />
Just my 2cp worth.
